t> <br> <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=27639.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=27639.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top  class=headings><font color=#333399>Author</font></td><td valign=top  class=headings><font color=#333399>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugeddine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Geddine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/17/02 9:55:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27639.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> FT and Mana Regen?</span><hr size=1> Just a question here.<br><br>I have read around the place that the Flowing Thought cap is set to 15, not this is not only a stacking cap but a hard cap.<br><br>Now Flowing Thought increases your mana regen by what ever FT number it is.  Now if the cap is 15, is it just for items with mana regen or is it all mana regen effects?<br><br>I'm looking at putting some AA points in Mental Clarity (I think thats it, the mana regen one)  after I do this would having 15 points of FT items.<br><br>I guess the BIG question is, what stacks with what, and whats the maximums when it comes to mana regen in all forms (items, AA Skills, Spells)? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urezinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rezinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/17/02 10:08:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27639.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FT and Mana Regen?</span><hr size=1> Can't be all effects. If at all it is only a ft cap. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubismuth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bismuth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/18/02 12:09:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27639.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FT and Mana Regen?</span><hr size=1> The cap on *latent effects* is 15 points of mana regen.  This includes all latent effects, such as Flowing Thought, 8th Shawl's Zephyr of Brell, etc.<br><br>The cap does NOT include the AA skill Mental Clarity (according to Jahaar, stated on Graffe's a few days back).  So with MC3 in mind, you could potentially have a latent 18 mana/tick regen.<br><br>The 15 cap also does NOT include spell buffs that provide mana regen, including clickable item effects of such nature (e.g., Lunar Whispers, Boon of Recovery, etc.).  Of course, these work just like normal spells with mana regen, like PoG, MotH, etc. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=83804">Rabbi Bismuth Jones</A><BR>60 Druid of Ytrilynth's Horde<BR>Zebuxoruk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujentrikenaspenbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jentriken Aspenbark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/18/02 12:14:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27639.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FT and Mana Regen?</span><hr size=1> the ft15 cap affects all worn items. does not affect mental clarity, buff spells, or sitting mana regen.<br><br>in the case where a worn item right clicks a mana regen spell using a buff slot (lunar whispers is a great example) it will stack.<br><br>edit: btw, i think the best mana regen you can get from spells and gear (period) is around 43. not counting bard songs as i don't know the exact mana count. assuming that it's 11, like c2, you'd get to 77 mana regen per tick sitting down. at a maximum<br><br>that's 15 for FT. 14 for KEI. 9 for potg and mots/h. 11 for bard song. 23 for sit. and 5 for boon of recovery/lunar whispers (that value is wrong, but close i think). 3 for MC.<br><br>it's close to 80 per tick anyways.<br><br>shamans on the other hand get over 100 per tick with torpor and canni.<br><br>really makes ya think.<br><br> <p>Venerable Jentriken Aspenbark<BR><BR>Retired Hierophant of Xegony</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujentrikenaspenbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jentriken Aspenbark</A> at: 6/18/02 2:45:49 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugeddine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Geddine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/18/02 5:23:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27639.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FT and Mana Regen?</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the confirmation guys. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaraden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saraden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/18/02 12:30:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27639.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FT and Mana Regen?</span><hr size=1> A little while back a lot of people were saying that the stated cap of 15 (stated by a Verant employee but can't recall which) was either untrue or not in place and there was no cap on FT.  Any word as to a change on that.  Also I have seen a lot of posts both ways about whether you can have FT items with the same level stack--ie having two FT 1 items you would only get the effect from one of them.  Some people say this is the case so that you must have items with different levels, while others say even items with the same level stack.  Anyone have hard data on this?  I'm really looking for an answer from someone who has done a controled study or a link to a controlled study not just &quot;it feels like they stack&quot; or I've read they do or don't stack.  Thanks.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukhardan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khardan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/18/02 1:08:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27639.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> &quot;Buff&quot; ft effects</span><hr size=1> Lunar Whispers don't stack with PoTg<br><br>Boon Of Recovery gets eaten by caannabalize <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujentrikenaspenbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jentriken Aspenbark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/18/02 3:32:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27639.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Buff&quot; ft effects</span><hr size=1> Saraden, it's very hard to do a controlled study on getting 1 mana extra per tick. it's very hard to notice.<br><br>from what i understand (this isn't what you want, take it anyways) ft1 will stack with ft1.<br><br>originally, before luclin, the ft cap was 15 for this reason:<br><br>ft1 didn't stack with ft1. and ft5 was best in game. so maxing out ft meant having ft1, ft2, ft3, ft4, ft5. it added up to 15.<br><br>then for a time, when they fixed that, there was no cap.<br><br>i've seen a post from verant on the wizzy boards somewhere saying there is a cap now, and MC bypasses it.<br><br>sorry i can't link it, it's fallen off the back of their board by now <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>the cap is pretty much known to be 15 now, this is a hard cap. see what i said earlier about what goes into it.<br><br>ft1 will stack with ft1. ft2 will stack with ft2. up to a max of 15 total.<br><br>hope that helps, i realize it isn't a controlled study, but it's common knowledge <p>Venerable Jentriken Aspenbark<BR><BR>Retired Hierophant of Xegony</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaraden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saraden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/18/02 5:43:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27639.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Buff&quot; ft effects</span><hr size=1> I do appreciate the response and agree that yes testing 1 point regen would be difficult especially given the fact that Verant refuses to make mana into a number like hit points.  However, prior to Luclin FT didn't stack at all--it was right at the time of Luclin that they made it stackable.  It was also at this time that a Verant employee was qouted as saying there was a cap of 15 on FT.  But I have read numberous times on boards that this cap simply does not exist though I have never seen someone post numbers supporting it.  I have found on many occasions that &quot;common knowledge&quot; is incorrect.  Given Verant's track record when it comes to stacking issues, etc. I just was hoping to see some hard evidence since there defiently are people out there still claiming that FT of the same level do not stack.  Like I said I do appreciate your response, I didn't mean to sound like an @#%$ demanding proof.  It's just soooooo often on EQ boards someone posts something based on their &quot;feeling&quot; or what they have heard or read elsewhere and they are totallly incorrect.<br> <p>Saraden 25th Ranger (Retired)<br>Gailen 57th Druid of KaranaGuildleader One Hundred Swords</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukhardan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khardan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/18/02 6:02:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27639.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.csun.edu/~hbcsc544/roscoes.gif width=75 height=70></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FT and Mana Regen?</span><hr size=1> For a full blown discussion on the topic, and some answers from people who have tested since the last patch go <a href=http://www.fohguild.org/forums/showthread.php?s=21de1de2c25b6727582be5c29c82c2e3&threadid=1543><b>here</b></a><br><br>http://www.fohguild.org/forums/showthread.php?s=21de1de2c25b6727582be5c29c82c2e3&threadid=1543 <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104127><img src=http://www.csun.edu/~hbcsc544/Moonsig.gif></a>Hierophant.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaraden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saraden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/19/02 5:42:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27639.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FT and Mana Regen?</span><hr size=1> Thank you for the link and there was a link from FoH board to the discussion on Graffe's site.  It provided the answers as follows:<br><br>FT of the same level stack though they initially did not.<br><br>The cap was just put in limiting FT to 15 including item effects such as the 8th shawl effect but not mental clarity or items with buff effects like emp robe.<br><br>Of course not a single post included any hard evidence hehe, just stated fact.  The only definitive post was the one saying that mental clarity does not count towards the 15 cap as the post came from Rich Waters.  I will however assume that these posts are correct and thank you guys for the input and link.<br> <p>Saraden 25th Ranger (Retired)<br>Gailen 57th Druid of KaranaGuildleader One Hundred Swords</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujentrikenaspenbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jentriken Aspenbark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/19/02 7:29:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27639.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FT and Mana Regen?</span><hr size=1> bah, i said the same thing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>and yes, the post i was referring to on the wizzy boards was the one where rich said MC stacks. <p>Venerable Jentriken Aspenbark<BR><BR>Retired Hierophant of Xegony</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=27639.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=27639.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27639.topic&index=11><img src=http://dev.thedruidsgrove.org/images/forum/addreplya.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=27639.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://p